cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about dialogue act tagging, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on spoken language understanding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for DA classification, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of training on multiple corpora to achieve robustness, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the topic of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it discusses the importance of creating a general representation of speakers' intents for open-domain human-machine interaction. Finally, the paper discusses the mapping of different annotation schemes to a standard, which falls under the subfield of software engineering (cs.SD).
